=== 2026-02-21 17:45 — Research: vaadin-boot custom servlet + H2 web console ===
- Researched two questions:
  1. How to register a custom servlet with vaadin-boot 13.6
  2. The H2 web console servlet class for Jakarta Servlet API

- vaadin-boot 13.6 API (decompiled from actual JARs in Gradle cache):
  - VaadinBoot extends VaadinBootBase<VaadinBoot>
  - Two approaches to add custom servlets:
    a. @WebServlet annotation auto-discovery (simplest — Jetty classpath scanning finds it)
    b. Override onStarted(WebAppContext) to programmatically add servlets after startup
  - onStarted(WebAppContext) is a protected method on VaadinBoot
  - WebAppContext.addServlet() has 4 overloads:
    - addServlet(String className, String pathSpec) -> ServletHolder
    - addServlet(Class<? extends Servlet>, String pathSpec) -> ServletHolder
    - addServlet(ServletHolder, String pathSpec) -> void
    - addServlet(HttpServlet, String pathSpec) -> ServletHolder
  - NO createWebAppContext() method in version 13.6 (that was from older docs/README)
  - JettyWebServer has getContext() -> WebAppContext (accessible after start)

- H2 web console servlet:
  - Class: org.h2.server.web.JakartaWebServlet (Jakarta Servlet API)
  - NOT org.h2.server.web.WebServlet (that's the javax.servlet version)
  - JakartaWebServlet extends jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet
  - Available in h2-2.2.224.jar (already a project dependency)
  - Init parameters passed as -flag value pairs to internal WebServer.init()

- Exact code for Main.kt provided to user (both approaches)
- No files changed
