=== 2026-02-22 19:14 — NAS directory structure exploration ===
- Explored //nas/PlexServedMedia/media/ disk hierarchy
- Documented top-level dirs: BLURAY, DVD, UHD, TV Series From Media, Family Movies
- TV Series: Show Name / Season NN / episode files (Plex-standard structure)
  - Some shows (Downton Abbey) are flat — all episodes in show root, no Season subdirs
  - Some shows (V The Miniseries, V The Final Battle) have no season dirs — files directly in show folder
  - Season 00 = specials/bonus content
- Movies (BLURAY/DVD/UHD): flat directories, no subdirs, one .mkv per movie
- File extensions: .mkv (dominant), .mp4 (rare — Arrival, Mummy trilogy), .nfo (XML metadata from DVDFab)
- Two naming generations observed:
  - Older transcodes: doubled name pattern "Show - S01E01 - Show - s01e01 - Episode Title" (DS9, Cheers)
  - Newer transcodes: clean pattern "Show - S01E01 - Episode Title" (Star Trek TOS, Wednesday, Firefly, Wheel of Time)
  - Some use year: "Star Trek Discovery (2017) - S01E01 - Title"
  - Miami Vice uses lowercase: "s01e01" instead of "S01E01"
- Movie naming: just title + extension, no year typically (exceptions: "Karate Kid The (1984)", "How To Train Your Dragon 2025")
  - Sequels: inconsistent numbering — "Die Hard (1)", "Austin Powers 1", "Star Wars 4", "Bourne (1) Identity"
  - UHD has MakeMKV artifacts: "_t00", "_t02" suffixes on some files
- .nfo files: DVDFab-generated XML, mostly empty for movies, populated with TMDB data for newer TV episodes
  - Movie .nfo: empty stub (no title, no year, no plot)
  - TV .nfo: has title, plot, season, episode, TMDB ID, actor info, poster URLs
- File sizes: DVD ~4-7 GB, BLURAY ~12-64 GB, UHD ~48-90 GB
