=== 2026-02-23 18:45 — Fix browser video playback (audio works, video blank) ===
- Root cause: TranscoderAgent used `-c:v copy` which preserved non-browser-safe codecs
  - DVD sources → MPEG-2 (browsers can't play)
  - UHD sources → HEVC/H.265 (browsers can't play)
  - Blu-ray sources → mostly H.264 (works fine)
- Fix: codec-aware transcoding in TranscoderAgent.kt
  - Added probeVideoCodec(): runs `ffmpeg -i` and parses "Video: <codec>" from stream info
  - Added isBrowserSafeCodec(): checks against {"h264", "avc1", "avc"}
  - H.264 sources: `-c:v copy` (fast, ~minutes)
  - Non-H.264 sources: `-c:v libx264 -preset medium -crf 18` (re-encode, slower but necessary)
- Startup cleanup: cleanupBadCodecFiles() runs once at TranscoderAgent start
  - Walks ForBrowser/ directory, probes each MP4's video codec
  - Deletes any with non-browser-safe codecs (+ associated VTT subtitle files)
  - Transcoder then re-processes them with correct encoding
- Verified: Cheers ForBrowser files (MPEG-2) deleted, Wednesday files (H.264) preserved
- Verified: Wednesday S01E01 plays in browser with video and audio
- Updated CLAUDE.md Video Playback section with codec-aware transcoding docs
- Files modified: TranscoderAgent.kt, CLAUDE.md
