=== 2026-03-01 — Fix movie/TV title mismatch in NAS scanner ===
- Problem: "Buffy the Vampire Slayer" exists as both MOVIE and TV. The NAS scanner
  matched all TV episodes to the movie because TranscodeMatcherService.matchByName()
  didn't consider media_type when disambiguating same-name titles.
- Step 1: UnlinkMovieEpisodesUpdater (one-time SchemaUpdater)
  - Finds MOVIE titles with >1 transcode (anomaly signal for mismatched TV episodes)
  - Deletes all transcodes + orphaned episodes for those movies
  - Deletes corresponding discovered_file records so next NAS scan re-processes them
  - Registered in Bootstrap.kt
- Step 2: TranscodeMatcherService media_type-aware disambiguation
  - matchMovie() passes MediaType.MOVIE, matchTvShow() passes MediaType.TV
  - disambiguate() now filters candidates to preferred media_type first
  - Falls back to all candidates if no same-type match exists
  - Added 5 new test cases: TV prefers TV title, movie prefers movie title,
    year+type combo, fallback when only wrong type exists, normalized+type
- Files changed:
  - service/UnlinkMovieEpisodesUpdater.kt (new)
  - service/TranscodeMatcherService.kt (modified: added preferredMediaType param)
  - Bootstrap.kt (register UnlinkMovieEpisodesUpdater)
  - TranscodeMatcherServiceTest.kt (added media type disambiguation tests)
- All tests pass
