=== 2026-03-06 — Roku SSDP + QR Pairing Debugging ===
End-to-end debugging of SSDP discovery and QR code pairing between
Roku channel and mediaManager server running in Docker on Synology NAS.

Docker networking:
- Switched to `network_mode: host` with port 16000 (avoids port 8080
  conflicts with Synology DSM). Removed `ports:` mappings from
  docker-compose.yml
- Added `--port` CLI flag to Main.kt for configurable listen port
- Dockerfile CMD reformatted to multi-line

SSDP fixes (SsdpResponder.kt):
- Explicit LAN interface selection: filter out docker*/veth/br- interfaces,
  join multicast on the first non-Docker interface with an IPv4 address
- Unicast response: send SSDP response via a fresh DatagramSocket bound to
  the LAN IP, not the multicast socket (fixes Roku not receiving responses)
- Fatal bind failure: System.exit(1) on BindException (port 1900 conflict
  with Synology UPnP)
- Suppress log noise from non-M-SEARCH SSDP packets (NOTIFY from other
  devices)

Roku PairTask.brs fixes:
- SSDP receive: bind to Roku's own IP (via roDeviceInfo.GetIPAddrs()),
  add notifyReadable(true), read data via udp.ReceiveStr() not msg.GetString()
- HTTP POST (pair/start): switched from sync PostFromString() to async
  AsyncPostFromString() + roUrlEvent — sync PostFromString returns HTTP code
  as integer, then GetResponseCode() crashes ("Member function not found")
- HTTP GET (pair/status poll): switched from sync GetToString() to async
  AsyncGetToString() + roUrlEvent for same reason
- Field ordering fix: set pairToken and pairUsername BEFORE pairStatus,
  because the pairStatus observer fires immediately on the render thread
  and needs token/username to already be populated. This was causing
  "Server URL and API key are required" error after successful pairing

Result: Full pairing flow working — SSDP discovery -> pair code -> QR display
  -> phone scan -> login -> confirmation -> token saved -> feed fetched

