=== 2026-03-15 18:00 — MediaSkipDetector: Tuning, capped comparisons, analysis history ===
- Replaced O(n^2) pairwise comparisons with capped hash-spread strategy:
  each episode compared against at most MaxComparisonCandidates (default 7)
  other episodes, spread across the season via FNV-1a hashing.
  Early exit on first valid match + skip already-matched episodes.
  20-episode season: worst case 140 comparisons instead of 190.
- All analysis tuning parameters now configurable via environment variables:
  MAX_FINGERPRINT_POINT_DIFFERENCES (6), MAX_TIME_SKIP (3.5),
  INVERTED_INDEX_SHIFT (2), MIN_INTRO_DURATION (15), MAX_INTRO_DURATION (120),
  MAX_COMPARISON_CANDIDATES (7), FINGERPRINT_LENGTH_SECONDS (120)
- AppConfig extended with init-only tuning properties, Program.cs reads env vars
- Plugin shim now initialized from AppConfig instead of bare defaults
- FpcalcService uses configurable FingerprintLengthSeconds
- Created docs/TUNING.md: documents all parameters, when to adjust, troubleshooting
- Updated secrets/example.env with commented-out tuning variables
- Added analysis history ring buffer (last 20) to ServerStatus
- Status page: color-coded analysis history table (green=found, gray=none, red=error)
  with time, directory, episodes, comparisons, outcome, elapsed columns
