=== 2026-03-15 19:15 — MediaSkipDetector: Fix fpcalc parsing, bump fingerprint length, UX ===
- Fixed FpcalcService.ParseJson: GetInt32() → GetUInt32(). fpcalc -raw outputs
  unsigned 32-bit integers; values like 3896246826 exceed Int32.MaxValue and threw
  FormatException. The uint32 type flows correctly through the entire pipeline:
  fpcalc → FpcalcResult → FingerprintCache (blob) → ChromaprintAnalyzer (XOR + PopCount).
- Bumped default FINGERPRINT_LENGTH_SECONDS from 120 to 600 (10 minutes, matching
  Jellyfin's AnalysisLengthLimit). 120s missed all Xena intros because they start
  at 3.5-6.7 minutes in (variable cold open lengths). 600s produces ~4825 points
  per file at ~6s/file vs ~948 points at ~1.2s/file.
- First successful detection: Xena S06, 21/22 intros found in 24 comparisons (0.4s).
  Intro segments ~60 seconds each, correctly varying start times per episode.
- Worker.FormatDirectoryDisplay: shows "Show / Season" in status page instead of
  bare season directory name.
- lifecycle/run-dev.sh: prints DB path and existence status on startup. Helped
  diagnose that DATA_DIR pointed to NAS, not local ./data.
