=== 2026-04-12 16:15 — Roku playback fix: Range chunk cap ===
- Investigated: Roku playback dying after a few seconds, reverting to title page
- Server logs (/admin/logs?logger=VideoStream) showed every STREAM entry capped
  at exactly 10.0 MiB with CancelledSubscriptionException warnings
- Root cause: VideoStreamHttpService caps Range responses at 10 MiB as a
  workaround for Armeria's default request timeout. Browsers with MediaSource
  Extensions re-range seamlessly; Roku's Video node treats response end as
  EOF and transitions to "finished"
- Researched Jellyfin for comparison: server returns PhysicalFileResult with
  EnableRangeProcessing=true — no cap, full requested range served in one
  response. Jellyfin's Roku client uses the same streamFormat="mp4" progressive
  playback as ours, so the difference is entirely server-side
- Fix in VideoStreamHttpService.kt: detect Roku via User-Agent, set a 6-hour
  request timeout up front, and skip the 10 MiB cap so Roku gets the full
  requested range on one response. Browsers unchanged
- Discovered RequestLogBuffer has no writer — /admin/requests is always empty.
  Noted for separate follow-up (not part of this fix)
- Deployed as docker image 202604121611 via lifecycle/docker-build.sh
- Files: src/main/kotlin/net/stewart/mediamanager/armeria/VideoStreamHttpService.kt
