=== 2026-04-13 15:55 — Zombie lease on server restart ===
- User reported a transcode lease persisting across a server restart
- Traced the flaw: on server redeploy, the JVM dies with active
  BuddySession objects in memory holding grace timers. Those timers
  never fire — the new JVM starts with an empty activeSessions map.
  Buddy reconnects, handleConnect finds no prior session (previousSession
  is null), takes no cleanup action. First message from the buddy hits
  renewLeases() which blanket-extends every CLAIMED/IN_PROGRESS lease
  under that buddy_name — including the ghost lease from pre-restart.
  Server sends a Connected message with resumable leases, but the buddy
  just logs the count and ignores them. No resumption protocol exists.
- Fix in BuddyGrpcService.handleConnect: when activeSessions.put returns
  null, call TranscodeLeaseService.releaseLeases(name) to kill any
  pre-existing orphaned leases under this buddy name. Normal reconnect
  within the 60s grace window is unaffected (previousSession is non-null,
  grace timer cancelled as before).
- Deployed as mediamanager:202604131549. The deploy itself exercises
  the fix — buddy reconnect triggered the orphan cleanup.
- Files: src/main/kotlin/net/stewart/mediamanager/grpc/BuddyGrpcService.kt
